### What's happening (short)

Your code determines that a Part-No is “missing” a particular DSI (e.g. `PF`) by checking a `PN_has_*` set that was built from `sheet3`. But when you mark rows red you mark **all occurrences** of that Part No in the sheet immediately — even if *some other occurrence later in the sheet* actually contains the expected DSI. In short: you mark before checking *all* occurrences for that Part No.

### The rule you want

Only mark a Part No as missing if **none** of its occurrences in `sheet3` have the expected DSI. Conversely, if any occurrence has the expected DSI, don't mark other occurrences as missing — instead only validate (red/green) the rows that actually have that DSI.

