### Why this fixes your specific symptom

The new `mark_missing_PN_red_for_desc` first scans the whole `sheet3` and determines whether **any** occurrence of a Part No has the expected DSI. Only when **none** of its occurrences do, it marks all rows for that Part No as missing. That prevents the earlier behavior of marking the first occurrence red even though a later occurrence has the correct DSI.

`compare_and_color` now only validates rows that actually carry the relevant DSI — it will color the row green if the nomenclature matches the expected description, otherwise red and attach a comment — but it will not blindly color other occurrences that do not carry that DSI.

